(12, '2014-05-08', '2014-05-13', 'Jane Smith', 'reviews', 'Tesla Model X deliveries delayed until next year', 'Tesla CEO Elon Musk has postponed initial deliveries of the Model X crossover to the second quarter of 2015.', '', 'Initially expected to arrive this year, Musk cited a shortage in battery cell supplies as the cause for the latest delay in his company’s earnings conference call.  According to AutoGuide, Musk also said production of the Model S is affected by the same shortage, but the company hopes to have it resolved by the third quarter of this year.\r\n\r\nAlthough its production specifications haven’t been announced, the Model X will reportedly clock a zero-to-100 km/h time below the five second mark and will be offered with a 60 kWh or an 85 kWh battery, like the Model S. In addition, the Model X concept’s most distinguishing feature, the Falcon Wing rear doors, will make it into production.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Initially expected to arrive this year, Musk cited a shortage in battery\r\n cell supplies as the cause for the latest delay in his company’s \r\nearnings conference call.  According to AutoGuide, Musk also said \r\nproduction of the Model S is affected by the same shortage, but the \r\ncompany hopes to have it resolved by the third quarter of this year.\r\n\r\nAlthough its production specifications haven’t been announced, the Model\r\n X will reportedly clock a zero-to-100 km/h time below the five second \r\nmark and will be offered with a 60 kWh or an 85 kWh battery, like the \r\nModel S. In addition, the Model X concept’s most distinguishing feature,\r\n the Falcon Wing rear doors, will make it into production.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Initially expected to arrive this year, Musk cited a shortage in battery\r\n cell supplies as the cause for the latest delay in his company’s \r\nearnings conference call.  According to AutoGuide, Musk also said \r\nproduction of the Model S is affected by the same shortage, but the \r\ncompany hopes to have it resolved by the third quarter of this year.\r\n\r\nAlthough its production specifications haven’t been announced, the Model\r\n X will reportedly clock a zero-to-100 km/h time below the five second \r\nmark and will be offered with a 60 kWh or an 85 kWh battery, like the \r\nModel S. In addition, the Model X concept’s most distinguishing feature,\r\n the Falcon Wing rear doors, will make it into production.', 'Tesla, Model X, Electric', 'tesla_model_x_deliveries_delayed_until_next_year'),
(15, '2014-05-12', '2014-05-13', 'Jeff Plungis', 'news', 'BMW reportedly planning front-wheel-drive Z2', 'Although it has been rumored for years, we could finally see BMW offer a front-wheel-drive roadster within the next two years.', '', '&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Although it has been rumored for years, we could finally see BMW offer a front-wheel-drive roadster within the next two years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.caranddriver.com/news/2017-bmw-z2-rendered-news&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Car and Driver&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;\r\n suggests BMW could expand its lineup with a roadster slotting below the\r\n Z4. Here’s the tough part to swallow: Known as the Z2, it will likely \r\nbe underpinned by the Mini Cooper’s UKL1 front-wheel-drive platform. &lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;As cringe-worthy as the idea of a \r\nfront-wheel-drive BMW is, the Z2 shows promise: the base model is \r\nexpected to be powered by the Mini Cooper’s turbocharged three-cylinder \r\nengine, while a turbo-four with anywhere between 160 to 230 horsepower \r\nis possible on higher-spec models. In addition, we could also see a Z2 M\r\n with about 300 horsepower, though we can’t imagine the torque steer.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Not only that, Car and Driver says BMW is \r\ntaking a no-frills approach in developing the Z2. For instance, it will \r\nlikely feature a traditional soft top, as opposed to a complex \r\npower-retractable roof like the Z4&amp;#8242;s. By focusing on saving weight, we \r\ncould see the Z2 tip the scales somewhere around 1,100 kg. As ironic as \r\nit is, this could be the modern-day “ultimate driving machine” BMW \r\nenthusiasts have been pining for. &lt;/p&gt;', 'Honda, Motorcyle, 2014 Honda F6C Valkyrie, Review', 'bmw_reportedly_planning_front_wheel_drive_z2'),
(16, '2014-05-12', '2014-05-13', 'Nick Tragianis', 'reviews', 'Honda expected to finally bring back the S2000 sports car', 'But it will be considerably different from the rear-wheel-drive roadster we last saw in 2009', '', '&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;It has been a while since Honda has offered a\r\n true sports car in its lineup, but a new report suggests the Japanese \r\nautomaker is considering a successor to the S2000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Speaking with a company insider, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/honda/86942/honda-s2000-to-be-reborn&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;AutoExpress&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;\r\n says the revived S2000 will be part of a three-pronged lineup of \r\nmid-engined sportscars from Honda. It will sit between the base S660, \r\nwhich was recently said to have been green-lit for production, and the \r\nflagship NSX.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;This time around, the S2000 is expected to \r\nbe a coupe rather than a convertible. Under the hood, the report says we\r\n can expect Honda’s new 2.0-litre turbocharged four-cylinder engine, but\r\n tuned to pump out 350 horsepower. AutoExpress says Honda officials are \r\nalso considering a hybrid, all-wheel-drive powertrain.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;If the rumours hold true, Honda’s S2000 successor is expected to launch sometime in 2017. &lt;/p&gt;', 'Honda, Motorcyle, 2014 Honda F6C Valkyrie, Review', 'honda_expected_to_finally_bring_back_the_s2000_sports_car'),
(17, '2014-05-12', '2014-05-13', 'Jeff Plungis', 'news', 'Ford recalls nearly 700,000 Escape SUVs and C-MAX hybrids over airbag risk', 'But it will be considerably different from the rear-wheel-drive roadster we last saw in 2009', 'http://wpmedia.driving.ca/2014/05/s2k.jpg?w=800&amp;amp;h=520&amp;amp;crop=1', '&lt;img src=&quot;http://wpmedia.driving.ca/2014/05/s2k.jpg?w=800&amp;amp;h=520&amp;amp;crop=1&quot; /&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;It has been a while since Honda has offered a\r\n true sports car in its lineup, but a new report suggests the Japanese \r\nautomaker is considering a successor to the S2000.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Speaking with a company insider, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/honda/86942/honda-s2000-to-be-reborn&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;AutoExpress&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;\r\n says the revived S2000 will be part of a three-pronged lineup of \r\nmid-engined sportscars from Honda. It will sit between the base S660, \r\nwhich was recently said to have been green-lit for production, and the \r\nflagship NSX.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;This time around, the S2000 is expected to \r\nbe a coupe rather than a convertible. Under the hood, the report says we\r\n can expect Honda’s new 2.0-litre turbocharged four-cylinder engine, but\r\n tuned to pump out 350 horsepower. AutoExpress says Honda officials are \r\nalso considering a hybrid, all-wheel-drive powertrain.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;If the rumours hold true, Honda’s S2000 successor is expected to launch sometime in 2017. &lt;/p&gt;', 'Ford, Recall, Escape, SUV, Hybrid', 'ford_recalls_nearly_700000_escape_suvs_and_cmax_hybrids_over_airbag_risk');

